      "message": "[Critical] Line 183: 🔴 Critical Issues - `now - lastDecrease_` is evaluated before checking whether `lastDecrease_` is initialized. Since `lastDecrease_` starts at `time_point::min()`, this can overflow the underlying steady_clock duration and produce undefined behavior. Check the sentinel first and only subtract for initialized timestamps.\n\n```suggestion\n    const bool hasDecrease \u003d lastDecrease_ !\u003d time_point::min();\n    auto secSinceDecrease \u003d hasDecrease ? std::chrono::duration\u003cfloat\u003e(now - lastDecrease_).count()\n                                       : std::numeric_limits\u003cfloat\u003e::infinity();\n\n    if (congestion \u003e cfg_.congestionThreshold) {\n        if (!hasDecrease || secSinceDecrease \u003e cfg_.decreaseCooldownSec) {\n            applyDecrease(congestion);\n        }\n```\n\nApply the same pattern anywhere a `time_point::min()` sentinel is subtracted.",
