      "message": "[Major] Line 660: 🟡 Suggestions - The new controller ignores non-sentinel REMB bitrate values. `check_RCTP_Info_REMB()` parses a `uint64_t* br`, but this code only reacts to `0x6803` and `0x7378`; if peers send a standard REMB bitrate estimate, it is silently discarded, regressing interoperability. Either keep the legacy sentinel path explicitly separated from standard REMB or clamp/apply real bitrate estimates.\n\n```suggestion\n        if (br \u003d\u003d 0x6803 || br \u003d\u003d 0x7378) {\n            auto newBitrate \u003d bwController_.onRembFeedback(br \u003d\u003d 0x6803);\n            setNewBitrate(newBitrate);\n        } else if (br \u003e 0) {\n            auto newBitrate \u003d static_cast\u003cunsigned\u003e(std::min\u003cuint64_t\u003e(br / 1000, videoBitrateInfo_.videoBitrateMax));\n            bwController_.setTargetBitrate(newBitrate);\n            setNewBitrate(newBitrate);\n        }\n```",
